President Obama has nominated Victoria F. Nourse to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit. Nourse is a law professor at the University of Wisconsin School of Law and has a background in criminal law, legislation, constitutional history, and the separation of powers. She is also known for her work in assisting then-Senator Joseph Biden in drafting the Violence Against Women Act. Nourse has held various positions throughout her career, including serving as a law clerk, litigation associate, assistant counsel, and special counsel. She has also held visiting professorships at several law schools. Nourse received her B.A. from Stanford University and her J.D. from the University of California, Boalt Hall School of Law.